               <head>Grant; Higham; 1313-1314</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111663">Higham</placeName>.
                        <origDate notBefore="1313" notAfter="1314">1313-1314</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> of <surname>Saham</surname>, of the parish of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Gaysle)</placeName>
                        </persName> to <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fyss</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Heyham)</placeName>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Fyss">Sarra his wife</persName>, for a sum of money, of an acre of arable land in the fields of Heyham, lying between the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Adam</forename> (the shepherd) '<surname>Bercar</surname>'</persName> and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Fader</surname></persName>, and abutting on the high road, towards the field called <placeName type="minor">Walhepes</placeName>, and on the heath called '<placeName type="minor">le Schottehetz</placeName>'.
                        Dated at <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Heyham)</placeName> on Thursday [14 March] after the feast of St Gregory, Pope. 7 Edw. II [1313-1314.]
                     Witnesses. <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Passelewe</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> the <surname type="patronymic">son of Thomas</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Passelewe</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Kersener</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Reginald</forename> of <surname>Gaysle</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>(Smith) Faber</surname></persName>', <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Sparke</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Howedene</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>.
                     The seal is wanting.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
